g of the K shakti, one does not be=\r\ncome spiritual, neither can it be said that if one has not had an experienc=\r\ne of the K shakti yet, one is not making progress spiritually. But by the t=\r\nime of the Hatha Yogic traditions, Nath Yogis, and Tantra, the understandin=\r\ng of spirituality became entirely Kundalini centric.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;3. Kundalini as=\r\n we read and hear of it today, IMO, is insufficiently understood. The maxim=\r\num that books or people speak of is the standard diagramAtic knowledge of c=\r\nhakras and Shakti rising up. Some correlation of this can be\n felt, but it =\r\nis in greatest depth still a mental concept and at times pretty vague and s=\r\npeculative. That is because this knowledge was passed down from capable gur=\r\nus to capable disciples, and it needed a blind adherence to the words of a =\r\nphysical Guru for the process of kundalinI sadhana to change a person into =\r\nsomeone truly spiritual. Hence the primacy of hanging on blindly to the Gur=\r\nu. The diagramtic linear understanding that we have of the K process has ga=\r\nps, and can very often give a lopsided view of things. For example the diag=\r\nram of a man sitting with chakras and Shakti rising up is actual a two-dime=\r\nnsional representation of a multidimensional phenomenon, highly prone to mi=\r\nsunderstanding. The influence of each of the chakras pervade the whole life=\r\n of a person. They overlap each other. Each represent psychological functio=\r\nns of the human organism. Activating or deactiving specific petals of each =\r\nchakra is important and vital for sadhana of each\n speicifc individual, whi=\r\nch a Guru can decide accurately. The diagramatic centers only represent the=\r\n focal point of that range of pyschological functions, but the sphere of in=\r\nfluence of each chakra can permeate into the whole system and consequently =\r\ninto life in general. It is impossible for any sadhaka to navigate the path=\r\n, with a K centric view of spirituality, unless guided constantly by a phys=\r\nical guru of great depth, knowledge and wisdom abouit Kundalini Yoga. Other=\r\nwise, like Columbus, one will start for India and end up reaching America.&lt;=\r\nbr&gt;&lt;br&gt;4. The concept of Guru and Shishya was always there, but in the Gita=\r\n and Upanishads, Guru was the Guru tattwa, which can manifest from an indiv=\r\nidual, or through anything provided the disciple is ready. Like Dattatreya =\r\nhad 24 non-human gurus. But this kind of concept of Guru is impractical whe=\r\nn it comes to Kundalini Yoga. One can become genuinely spiritual by contemp=\r\nlating and trying to imbibe the advice of\n Krishna in the Gita without a ph=\r\nysical Guru. Same cannot be done in Kundalini centric view of sadhana.&lt;br&gt;&lt;=\r\nbr&gt;5. In the Gita tradition, or for that matter any spiritual tradition, Ku=\r\nndalini will awaken for sure, but since spirituality is not looked at from =\r\nthat prism, therefore this process is left to Nature to happen on its own, =\r\nwhen a sadhaka is ready internally. Moreover, the judgement of spirituality=\r\n - whether a person is spiritual or non-spiritual - cannot be made based me=\r\nrely on an experience of Kundalini itself. Until the K shakti rises up to m=\r\neet the higher spiritual realms and brings down those energies into life, a=\r\nnd then those energies settle down into the system, actual spiritual effect=\r\ns may not be visible.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;6. The Kundalini is the force of the pranamaya=\r\nkosha which holds the external personality together. The aim is to liberate=\r\n it from its mundane function and make it shoot-up to purify itself. Every =\r\ntime it comes into contact with the\n higher planes, it imbibes the energies=\r\n and bring them down into life. The pranamayakosha is pure shakti, constant=\r\nly in motion. This is a tremendous force. Because Force in its original nat=\r\nure is the domain of the Mother, the dynamic aspect of Sat-Chit-Ananda, the=\r\nrefore Kundalini is called Shakti sadhana or Mother Kundalini.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;7. In=\r\n the light of the above points, it can be fairly understood why the Gita pu=\r\nts its trust on Purushottama, while the Tantras - whose spiritual prism was=\r\n Kundalini centric - puts the focus on Adya Shakti.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;8. In this age w=\r\nhen Guurus are rare, genuine paramparas are rarer still, and capable sadhak=\r\ns are negligible, a Kundalini centric view of sadhana can be detrimental fo=\r\nr most people.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;9. Of course, these are my view-point as I see it. Fe=\r\nel free to disagree.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;-Regards&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;Rajarshi&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/=\r\nspan&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;div class=3D&quot;MsoNorm=\r\nal&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span\n class=3D&quot;Apple-style-span&quot; style=3D&quot;font-size:16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span=\r\n class=3D&quot;Apple-style-span&quot; style=3D&quot;color:rgb(153, 153, 153);&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;=\r\n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span class=3D&quot;yui_3_2_0_2_134243527249950&quot; style=3D&quot;font-family=\r\n:times new roman, new york, times, serif;&quot;&gt;awaktam wyaktimApannam manyantE =\r\nmAmabuddhayah |&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class=3D&quot;yui_3_2_0_2_134243506227946 yui=\r\n_3_2_0_2_134243527249952 yui_3_7_2_27_1353650678498_67&quot; style=3D&quot;FONT-SIZE:=\r\n10pt;COLOR:navy;FONT-FAMILY:Verdana;&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Times=\r\n New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div&gt; param bhAwamajAnanto mamAwyayamanuttamam ||[7:24]&lt;/d=\r\niv&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;  &lt;div style=\r\n=3D&quot;font-family: Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-serif; font-=\r\nsize: 12pt;&quot;&gt; &lt;div style=3D&